<h3>Profile</h3>

<p>
Self-driven software engineer with hands-on experience developing, testing, and
maintaining production applications across the full software development lifecycle.
I hold a First-Class Honours degree in Software Engineering from Nottingham Trent
University and currently work at Microlise, where I deliver features, security fixes,
and defect resolution within Agile, cross-functional teams.
</p>

<p>
Proficient in C#, TypeScript, SQL, and related technologies, with practical
experience building Angular applications from initial requirements through backend
and frontend implementation. I take ownership of the work I deliver — from writing
user stories and tasks through to deployment — and apply Lean principles alongside
Agile practices to ship reliable, well-tested software.
</p>

<p>
Strong problem-solver with a focus on debugging, performance optimisation, and
improving user experience. Comfortable collaborating with diverse teams and
external stakeholders, and equally effective working independently to drive features
from concept to completion.
</p>

