<h3>Projects</h3>

<article id="wheres-my-tutor">
<h4>Where's My Tutor</h4>
<p class="meta">Android · Java · Firebase · Google Maps</p>
<p>
Developed an Android app to enhance productivity and facilitate effective time
management for both students and staff members at the university. The
application catered to two distinct user groups, students and staff, offering
lecturers the capability to broadcast their location through GPS or manually set
it using Google Maps for students. Additionally, the app enabled users to
schedule and monitor meetings, specifying details such as timeframes and
locations. It features a notification system that alerts recipients upon
receiving a meeting request. This project afforded me valuable insights into
the Android platform, Firebase, GPS location services, and the integration of
the Google Maps API.
</p>
<p class="meta">University module: Mobile Platform Applications (1EXC)</p>
</article>

